MAMELODI Sundowns Diski Challenge team snapped their five games winless run in the DStv Diski Challenge with an impressive 4-2 win over Royal AM at Princess Magogo Stadum on Saturday. The young Brazilians had to play the last 25 minutes of the game with ten men after their captain Christopher Mbhele was sent off for a challenge which left him injured. Mbhele received his red card while he was being stretched off the pitch in what appeared to be a calf injury. The red card afforded abafana bakamaMkhize a chance to spark a comfortable comeback but their efforts were in vain despite creating a number of chances. The first half saw the two teams scoring five goals. Sundowns dominated the early exchanges of the game and capitalized on their chances finding the back of the net three times in less than 20 minutes. It was Ndzalama Mhangwana who set the tone fpopor Downs dinding the opener in the second minute of the match. Thato Matli doubled their lead after eight minutes into the game. Mbhele who was later sent off in the game extended their lead in the 18th minute with a glancing diving header. Real kings managed to get in the rhythm and pulled one back when Xolani Phewa headed the ball into the back of an empty net in the 23rd minute. Philani Khumalo scored a superb free-kick at the stroke of halftime to give his team a chance for a comeback against another Pretorian side. Oageng Phiri scored the only goal of the second half off the bench to help ease the pressure for coach Surprise Moririâ€™s men. The victory moved Sundowns to 4th on the log with 23 points after 14 games. Royal AM remains 9th on the log with 17 points.